LIFE is beautiful, but only for those who have good health and freedom. So the saying goes. However, though not in any way incarcerated, beautiful Adenike Kareem, a civil servant with the Kwara State government, is neither healthy nor free to move around. Reason? She suffers from excruciating rectal cancer and is thus bedridden. On May 28, 2018, 46-year-old Adenike was diagnosed with colon rectal cancer at the University of Ilorin Teaching Hospital (UITH.)   Glo Battle of the Year: GloTV now open to ALL networks     Oluwo unveils new queen as they get married in Kano     How I prevented full blown physical combat between Bianca,…   Already, she has undergone three surgeries but needs to go through a fourth and vital one to cross the final hurdle. She therefore needs the sum of Five million naira (N5m) urgently, to undergo the surgery, at the University of Ilorin Teaching Hospital. Doctors in charge of her case are Professor Olatoke and Dr Aboderin. Kind-hearted Nigerians, individuals and corporate organisations can make their donations to: Kareem Adenike’s GTB account number, 0034636609. Telephone: 08060909031